metadata.name: MAGNETIK #229
metadata.description:
The output of MAGNETIK reminds me of what tornadoes do to our cities and buildings, yet I imagine the pieces that are about to break off and fly away to be made of metal foil and they do so because of a magnetic force that is pulling them away from where they belong…  This one is also a charity run :  
- 20% of the primary sales will go directly to the Processing Foundation, 

- Remaining 80% will be donated to a group of individuals that raise money to buy computers for less fortunate architecture students in a university in the eastern part of Turkey. Please read the next paragraph for a detailed explanation

- I will decide what to do with the secondary sales later if there will be any.

About the majority (80%) of the donation : I decided that the donations should be done in a double-blind way, the donator does not know who they are donating to, and the receivers of the donation will not know from whom the donation is coming from, hence I will transfer the funds these individuals mentioned to act as a middle-step. I feel like this is a hard thing to provide a solid proof for, so I recommend if you have doubts and/or straight away do not trust me or this process, do not mint. I will only be able to provide proof of transfer of funds to a third-party. I trust the people I am sending the funds to, we have done this before (not to brag or anything) and I know that we are affecting younger people’s life in a good way. Also, I believe that the funds raised from this project alone will not be enough to buy one decent config. computer by itself, if it were so, I would have done it differently.  About MAGNETIK :  
MAGNETIK plays on the idea of distorting and breaking grids by employing an illusion of fake 3D and tries to make the resulting composition look good with rhythm and color harmony.
 
- 21 palettes,
- 2 background modes : lights on / lights off,
- 3 grid types,
- plus some surprise features…

I encourage you to try and see the variations before minting :)  2 of the grid types are based on https://gorillasun.de/blog/an-algorithm-for-irregular-grids by Ahmad Moussa ( https://twitter.com/gorillasu ) and used with his knowledge and kind permission.

gradient formulas are based on https://twitter.com/takawo/status/1505876107492720651?s=20&t=S9aU_oNYyjBieBcEmvUV-g
by Takawo Shunsuke ( https://twitter.com/takawo ) and used with his knowledge and kind permission.

Thank you all in advance and have a good day!

DISCLAIMER : I am not a good coder, I have tried to fix my past mistakes from my earlier projects to make some room for new mistakes :) I am hoping that there isn’t any huge bugs or anything left so you can enjoy your mint! Please hit me up if you have any concerns after minting and we can discuss a solution.

metadata.name: Cables and Clouds #185
metadata.description:
Capturing clouds... an old dream of mad scientist... coming true...
But wait... are they real clouds ? Maybe... maybe not...
Is it the real life ?
Is this just fantasy ?

Interaction.
Press h in live mode to list the possibilities.
Key 's'  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key 'c' to change color palette
Key 'd' to toggle a special color mode to highlight the different components (and have the number of points used in your specific drawing).

Features.
18 different features displayed (format, color palettes, main elements characteristics, rare elements...).

metadata.name: twofiftythousand #107
metadata.description:
twofiftythousand is about the chaos of unlimited decisions. Look for a pattern in the noise.

Press 's' to save an image while in full-screen mode.

If you want to increase the resolution of the saved image, add e.g. &size=2000 after the live/fullscreen view URL to render the canvas at that specific pixel width (default = browser sized). This will be dependent on your system specifications, but outputs of up to 8000px wide, or above, should be possible.

metadata.name: Daydreamer #78
metadata.description:
‘For the artist communication with nature remains the most essential condition. The artist is human, himself nature; part of nature within natural space.’ (Paul Klee, 1944) 


Working on long-form nature has an interesting side effect. On the one hand, you're attempting a shallow imitation of a landscape.... You are working with cold logic and code, vainly trying to control randomness to create this virtual facsimile, something you know is artificial.... 

....and yet.... even with all this left-brain activity, your right-brain pushes back, and imagines being there. While working on this project I found myself continually daydreaming, wandering off to hear the sounds of waterfalls, or the crunch of walking along a sandy lake shore. If you've ever wondered about coding, I urge you to learn. Daydreams await....


Press '1' once rendering is finished, to redraw at 5120x5120 resolution 
Press '2' to export without post-processing effects 

3rd party libraries (license text and links included in source) 
- p5.js - Creative coding framework 
- JS Topology Suite "JSTS", a port of Java Topology Suite "JTS" - High-level Geometry library 
- WebGLImageFilter, Dominic Szablewski - phoboslab.org 

I have tried to use soft blurs and shadows to give a sense of layering and depth to the scene. After viewing for a while, it reminds me of 3D paper-art. There are traits for colour and amount of birds, waterfalls, etc. but none are especially rare – These properties are intended for filtering the collection.

metadata.name: Puzzles of the mind #117
metadata.description:
This is abstract art based on mathematical structure.
The puzzle of your mind seems broken and rearranged.

Mode has 2 variations.
 - Normal
 - Black
Color has 3 variations.
 - 常磐-tokiwa- (Green)
 - 真朱-shinshu- (Red)
 - 紺碧-konpeki- (Blue)
Color Level has 2 variations.
 - High
 - Low
Square Size has 3 variations.
 - Small
 - Middle
 - Large

Tokiwa is a Japanese word meaning always the same. It's green like the color of evergreen leaves.

Shinshu is a Japanese word that refers to a dull red color like vermilion. It means vermilion in its natural state with nothing mixed in.

Konpeki is a Japanese word that describes a deep blue, very close to azure. It's like a clear sky with summer sunshine.

Controls (in live view):
 - Press [f] to switch full screen on and off
 - Press [s] to download a PNG file with windowsize
 - Press [l] to download a PNG file with large size 4800 pixel (wait a minutes)

Create with p5.js
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Flow #396
metadata.description:
Flow is a collection of eye pleasing formula's in the form of patterns and colors.

Features include:
- Patterns
- Palettes
- Focus points
- Margins
- Sizes
- Spacings
- Color distribution patterns
- Modifiers
- Gradients
- Dots
- Overflow

Due to the large amount of calculations it may take a few seconds to generate.
The spinning indicator on the top right disappears when it is finished, this is the best moment to save.

Press [s] to save a high resolution PNG @ 9933x14043 pixels (A0 paper dimensions @ 300 DPI).

Flow By @OneDayOfCrypto, 2022

metadata.name: Kinetic Bug #205
metadata.description:
Best viewed on a decent GPU,  because physics simulations are performance intensive. Otherwise you might encounter a bug...

In a world of digital data, a new life is born. We are not alone...
Explore how kinetic bugs make their way through the world. What will their destiny be?
It's curious that we can sympathize to a predefined creature living it's predestined life in the digital world. Coding in the computer abyss reveals interesting worlds.

Keyboard
[ space ] - jump
[ click ] - increase velocity briefly
[ r ] - restart simulation
[ s ] - save image
[ f ] - full screen

Mobile
[ two finger tap ] - jump
[ tap ] - increase velocity briefly

Created with Three.js + rapier.js
Copyright (c) July 2022 Shaderism

metadata.name: Traffic #88
metadata.description:
Traffic is a companion piece to Scaffold. Whilst Scaffold was intended to capture a moment in time of a single mind, Traffic aims to represent a shared moment in a community.

Outputs can be beautiful, but can also be chaotic. They can be comprised of many contributions, but a single voice may drown out many others.

All royalties go to the original minter.

Keyboard commands:

s - save as png
h - toggle high resolution 
b - toggle background texture
a - switch aspect ratio
r - new moment
